---
title: Sweet Potato and Black Bean Tacos with Avocado Crema and Cilantro
description: Not many tacos can boast that they’re rich in vitamin A. Ours, however, are full of it, thanks to tender roasted cubes of sweet potato. They’re joined by black beans and a zesty avocado crema for some of the most delectable veggie goodness to be found inside the fold of a tortilla. You could say that they bring their A-game in every single way.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5b47a46b30006c0de316d802-8bfc3c25.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/sweet-potato-and-black-bean-tacos-5b47a46b30006c0de316d802-f131f12e.pdf
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-potato-and-black-bean-tacos-5b47a46b30006c0de316d802
author: Michelle Doll Olson
nutrition:
  calories: 820 kcal
  fat: 35 g
  saturated fat: 10 g
  carbohydrates: 104 g
  sugar: 17 g
  protein: 16 g
  fiber: 20 g
  sodium: 710 mg
course: main course
time required: 40 minutes
cuisine: Fusion
---

Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 400 degrees. Cut @sweet potatoes{2} into ½-inch cubes. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with 1 TBSP @olive oil{2%tbsp} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast in oven until tender and lightly browned, about ~{20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and diced). Pick @cilantro{¼%oz} leaves from stems; discard stems. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Drain and rinse half the @black beans{6.7%oz} from the can (use the rest as you like). Zest ½ tsp zest from @lime{1}, then cut into halves.

Heat 1 TBSP olive oil in a large #pan{} over medium heat. Add onion and cook, tossing occasionally, until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Add garlic and beans to pan. Cook, tossing, until fragrant and warmed through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in #foil{} and place in oven to warm, about ~{5%minutes}.

> TIP: Alternatively, wrap tortillas in a damp paper towel and microwave on high until warm, about 30 seconds.

Toss sweet potatoes, @honey{½%oz}, @cumin{1%tsp}, and juice from one lime half into pan with beans and cook until liquid is mostly evaporated, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Halve, pit, and peel @avocado{1}. Cut one half into thin slices. Roughly chop other half and place in a #medium bowl{} along with @sour cream{4%tbsp}, juice from remaining lime half, and lime zest. Mash with a #fork{} until mostly smooth. Season with salt and pepper.

Spread avocado crema onto tortillas, then top each with filling, avocado slices, and cilantro.

> TIP: Break out the hot sauce if you like it spicy.